summary: The "moviepage.css" file contributes to the system by defining the styling for various elements on the movie page. It introduces styles for the rating box, poster, top header, logo, menu, menu options, iframe, summary section, rating display, submit button, and video container. These styles include positioning, sizing, fonts, colors, transitions, and hover effects. The file enhances the visual presentation of the movie page and adds interactive elements such as star ratings and menu options. The styles defined in this file help create a cohesive and visually appealing user interface for the movie page within the larger software system.
